{{ThisDateInRecentYears}} 
{{Day}}

==Events==
*[[1183]] &amp;ndash; [[Taira no Munemori]] and the [[Taira]] clan take the young [[Emperor Antoku]] and the [[Imperial Regalia of Japan|three sacred treasures]] and flee to western [[Japan]] to escape pursuit by the [[Minamoto]] clan. (Traditional [[Japanese calendar|Japanese date]]: Twenty-fifth Day of the Seventh Month of the Second Year of [[Juei]]).
*[[1385]] &amp;ndash; [[1383-1385 Crisis|Portuguese Crisis of 1383–1385]]: [[Battle of Aljubarrota]] &amp;ndash; [[Portugal|Portuguese]] forces commanded by [[John I of Portugal|King João I]] and his [[General officer|general]] [[Nuno Álvares Pereira]] defeat the [[Castile (historical region)|Castilian]] army of [[John I of Castile|King Juan I]].
*[[1592]] &amp;ndash; [[Imjin War]]: [[Battle of Hansando]] Admiral [[Yi Sun-sin]] decisively defeats the Japanese Navy at Hasan Island.
*[[1598]] &amp;ndash; [[Nine Years War (Ireland)|Nine Years War]]: [[Battle of the Yellow Ford]] &amp;ndash; [[Ireland|Irish]] forces under [[Hugh O'Neill, 2nd Earl of Tyrone|Hugh O'Neill]], [[Earl]] of [[County Tyrone|Tyrone]], defeat an [[England|English]] expeditionary force under [[Henry Bagenal]].
*[[1816]] &amp;ndash; the United Kingdom formally annexed the [[Tristan da Cunha]] archipelago, ruling them from the [[Cape Colony]] in South Africa.
*[[1842]] &amp;ndash; [[Indian Wars]]: [[Seminole Wars|Second Seminole War]] ends, with the [[Seminole (tribe)|Seminoles]] forced from [[Florida]] to [[Oklahoma]].
*[[1846]] &amp;ndash; The [[Cape Girardeau, Missouri|Cape Girardeau]] meteorite, a 2.3 [[kilogram|kg]] chondrite-type [[meteorite]] strikes near the town of [[Cape Girardeau, Missouri|Cape Girardeau]] in [[Cape Girardeau County, Missouri|Cape Girardeau County]], [[Missouri]].
*[[1848]] &amp;ndash; [[Oregon Territory]] is organized by [[act of Congress]].
*[[1880]] &amp;ndash; Construction of [[Cologne Cathedral]], the most famous landmark in [[Cologne]], [[Germany]], is completed.
*[[1885]] &amp;ndash; [[Japan|Japan's]] first [[patent]] is issued to the inventor of a rust-proof paint.
*[[1888]] &amp;ndash; A [[recording]] of English composer [[Arthur Sullivan]]'s [[The Lost Chord]], one of the first recordings of music ever made, is played during a press conference introducing [[Thomas Edison]]'s [[phonograph]] in [[London]].
*[[1893]] &amp;ndash; [[France]] introduces motor vehicle registration.
*[[1897]] &amp;ndash; The town of Anosimena is captured by [[France|French]] troops from [[Menabe]] defenders in [[Madagascar]].
*[[1900]] &amp;ndash; A joint European-[[Japan]]ese-[[United States]] force ([[Eight-Nation Alliance]]) occupies [[Beijing]], in a campaign to end the bloody [[Boxer Rebellion]] in [[China]].
*[[1901]] &amp;ndash; The first claimed [[aviation|powered flight]], by [[Gustave Whitehead]] in his [[Number 21 (plane)|Number 21]].
*[[1908]] &amp;ndash; The first [[beauty contest]] is held in [[Folkestone]], England.
*[[1911]] &amp;ndash; [[United States Senate]] leaders [[Presidents pro tempore of the United States Senate, 1911-1913|agree to rotate the office]] of [[President pro tempore of the United States Senate|President pro tempore of the Senate]] among leading candidates to fill the vacancy left by [[William P. Frye]]'s death.
*[[1912]] &amp;ndash; [[United States]] [[U.S. Marines|Marines]] invade [[Nicaragua]] to support the [[United States|U.S.]]-backed government installed there after [[José Santos Zelaya]] had resigned three years earlier.
*[[1916]]&amp;ndash;[[Romania]] declares war on [[Austro-Hungary]], joining Antante in World War I
*[[1921]] &amp;ndash; [[Tannu Tuva]], later [[Tuvinian People's Republic]] is established as a completely independent country (which is supported by [[Russian SFSR|Soviet Russia]]).
*[[1925]] &amp;ndash; The original Hetch Hetchy [[Moccasin, Tuolumne County, California|Moccasin]] Powerhouse is completed and goes on line.
*[[1933]] &amp;ndash; Loggers cause a [[forest fire]] in the [[Pacific Coast Ranges|Coast Range]] of [[Oregon]], later known as the first forest fire of the [[Tillamook Burn]]. It is extinguished on [[September 5]], after destroying 240,000 acres (970&amp;nbsp;km²).
*[[1935]] &amp;ndash; [[United States]] [[Social Security (United States)|Social Security]] Act passes, creating a government pension system for the retired.
*[[1936]] &amp;ndash; [[Rainey Bethea]] is hanged in [[Owensboro, Kentucky|Owensboro]], [[Kentucky]] in the last public [[capital punishment in the United States|execution in the United States]].
*[[1937]] &amp;ndash; Chinese Air Force Day:  The beginning of [[air-to-air combat]] of the [[War of Resistance|Second Sino-Japanese War]] and [[World War II]] in general, when 6 Imperial Japanese [[Mitsubishi G3M]] bombers are shot down by the [[Republic of China Air Force|Nationalist Chinese Air Force]] while raiding Chinese air bases.
*[[1941]] &amp;ndash; [[World War II]] &amp;ndash; [[Winston Churchill]] and [[Franklin D. Roosevelt]] sign the [[Atlantic Charter]] of war stating postwar aims.
*[[1945]] &amp;ndash; [[Japan]] accepts the Allied [[Japanese Instrument of Surrender|terms of surrender]] in [[World War II]] and the [[Emperor of Japan|Emperor]] records the [[Gyokuon-hoso|Imperial Rescript on Surrender]] ([[August 15]] in [[Japan standard time]]).
*[[1947]] &amp;ndash; [[Pakistan]] gains [[Independence of Pakistan|Independence]] from the [[British Empire|British]] [[Indian Empire]] and joins the [[Commonwealth of Nations]].
*[[1948]] &amp;ndash; [[Don Bradman]], widely regarded as the best cricket batsman in history, makes a [[duck (cricket)|duck]] in [[Fifth Test, 1948 Ashes series|his final Test innings]].
*[[1959]] &amp;ndash; Founding and first official meeting of the [[American Football League]].
*[[1967]] &amp;ndash; [[United Kingdom|UK]] [[Marine Broadcasting Offences Act]] declares participation in offshore [[pirate radio]] illegal.
*[[1969]] &amp;ndash; [[United Kingdom|British]] troops are deployed in [[Northern Ireland]].
*[[1972]] &amp;ndash; An [[East Germany|East German]] [[Ilyushin Il-62]] crashes during takeoff from [[East Berlin]], killing 156.
*[[1973]] &amp;ndash; [[Constitution of Pakistan|The constitution of 1973]] comes into effect in [[Pakistan]]
*[[1974]] &amp;ndash; 126 [[Turkish Cypriots]] are [[Maratha, Santalaris and Aloda massacre|massacred]] in the villages of [[Maratha, Cyprus|Maratha]], [[Santalaris]] and [[Aloda, Cyprus|Aloda]].
*[[1976]] &amp;ndash; The [[Senegal]]ese [[political party]] ''[[African Independence Party-Renewal|PAI-Rénovation]]'' is legally recognized. PAI-Rénovation thus becomes the third legal party in the country.
*[[1980]] &amp;ndash; [[Lech Wałęsa]] leads strikes at the [[Gdańsk]], [[Poland]] shipyards.
*[[1987]] &amp;ndash; All the children held at Kia Lama, a rural property on [[Lake Eildon]], Australia, run by the [[Santiniketan Park Association]], are released after a police raid.
*[[1994]] &amp;ndash; [[Ilich Ramírez Sánchez]], also known as &quot;''[[Carlos the Jackal]]'',&quot; is captured.
*[[2003]] &amp;ndash; [[2003 North America blackout|Widescale power blackout]] in the northeast [[United States]] and [[Canada]].
*[[2006]] &amp;ndash; [[Chencholai bombing]] in which 61 Tamil girls are killed in Sri Lankan Airforce bombing.
*[[2007]] &amp;ndash; The [[2007 Kahtaniya bombings]] kills at least 796 people.
*[[2010]] &amp;ndash; 2010 [[Summer Youth Olympic Games]], first ever Youth Olympics, officially starts in [[Singapore]].

