==Religious figures==
* [[Adrian of Nicomedia]], Herculian Guard of the Roman Emperor Galerius Maximian
* [[Adrian of Canterbury]], scholar and the Abbot of St Augustine's Abbey in Canterbury
* [[Adrian of May]], Scottish saint and martyr from the Isle of May, martyred by Vikings, 875
* [[Adrian of Poshekhon]], Russian Orthodox saint, hegumen of Dormition monastery in Yaroslavl region
* [[Adrian of Monza]], Russian Orthodox saint, see May 5 (Eastern Orthodox liturgics)
* [[Adrian of Ondrusov]], Russian Orthodox saint and wonder-worker
* [[San Adrian (tunnel)]] and hermitage, a landmark in the Way of St. James
* [[Adrian Helmet]] was a combat helmet issued to the French Army during World War I

