{{pp-move-indef}}{{AugustCalendar|float=right}}
{{ThisDateInRecentYears}} 
{{Day}}

==Events==
* [[778]] &amp;ndash; The [[Battle of Roncevaux Pass]], at which [[Roland]] is killed.
* [[927]] &amp;ndash; The [[Saracen]]s conquer and destroy [[Taranto]].
* [[982]] &amp;ndash; [[Holy Roman Emperor]] [[Otto II of Germany|Otto II]] is defeated by the Saracens in the battle of [[Capo Colonna]], in [[Calabria]]
*[[1018]] &amp;ndash; Byzantine general [[Eustathios Daphnomeles]] blinds and captures [[Ibatzes of Bulgaria]] by a ruse, thereby ending Bulgarian resistance against Emperor [[Basil II]]'s conquest of [[First Bulgarian Empire|Bulgaria]].
*[[1040]] &amp;ndash; King [[Duncan I of Scotland|Duncan I]] is killed in battle against his first cousin and rival [[Macbeth of Scotland|Macbeth]]. The latter succeeds him as [[King of Scotland]].
*[[1057]] &amp;ndash; King [[Macbeth of Scotland|Macbeth]] is killed at the [[Battle of Lumphanan]] by the forces of [[Malcolm III of Scotland|Máel Coluim mac Donnchada]].
*[[1185]] &amp;ndash; The cave city of [[Vardzia]] is consecrated by Queen [[Tamar of Georgia]].
*[[1248]] &amp;ndash; The [[Cornerstone|foundation stone]] of [[Cologne Cathedral]], built to house the [[Shrine of the Three Kings at Cologne Cathedral|relics of the]] [[Biblical Magi|Three Wise Men]], is laid. (Construction is eventually completed in [[1880]].)
*[[1261]] &amp;ndash; [[Michael VIII Palaeologus]] is crowned [[Byzantine emperor]] in [[Constantinople]].
*[[1309]] &amp;ndash; [[The city of Rhodes]] surrenders to the forces of the [[Knights of St. John]], completing their conquest of [[Rhodes]]. The knights establish their headquarters on the island and rename themselves the [[Knights of Rhodes]].
*[[1430]] &amp;ndash; [[Francesco Sforza]], lord of Milan, conquers [[Lucca]].
*[[1461]] &amp;ndash; The [[Empire of Trebizond]] surrenders to the forces of [[Sultan Mehmet II]]. This is regarded by some historians as the real end of the [[Byzantine Empire]]. Emperor [[David of Trebizond|David]] is exiled and later murdered.
*[[1483]] &amp;ndash; [[Pope Sixtus IV]] consecrates the [[Sistine Chapel]].
*[[1517]] &amp;ndash; Seven [[Portugal|Portuguese]] armed [[vessels]] led by [[Fernão Pires de Andrade]] meet [[China|Chinese]] officials at the [[Pearl River estuary]].
*[[1519]] &amp;ndash; [[Panama City]], [[Panama]], is founded.
*[[1534]] &amp;ndash; Saint [[Ignatius of Loyola]] and six classmates take initial vows, leading to the creation of the [[Society of Jesus]] in September 1540.
*[[1537]] &amp;ndash; [[Asunción]], [[Paraguay]], is founded.
*[[1540]] &amp;ndash; [[Arequipa]], [[Peru]], is founded.
*[[1549]] &amp;ndash; [[Society of Jesus|Jesuit]] [[priest]] Saint [[Francis Xavier]] comes ashore at [[Kagoshima]] (Traditional [[Japanese calendar|Japanese date]]: July 22, 1549).
*[[1599]] &amp;ndash; [[Nine Years War (Ireland)|Nine Years War]]: [[Battle of Curlew Pass]] &amp;ndash; Irish forces led by [[Hugh Roe O'Donnell]] successfully ambush English forces, led by [[Sir Conyers Clifford]], sent to relieve Collooney Castle.
*[[1695]] &amp;ndash; [[Early Modern France|French]] forces end the [[Bombardment of Brussels]], leaving a third of the buildings in the city in ruins.
*[[1760]] &amp;ndash; [[Seven Years' War]]: [[Battle of Liegnitz (1760)|Battle of Liegnitz]] &amp;ndash; [[Frederick the Great]]'s victory over the [[Austrians]] under [[Ernst Gideon Freiherr von Laudon|Ernst von Laudon]].
*[[1824]] &amp;ndash; Freed [[United States|American]] slaves found [[Liberia]].
*[[1843]] &amp;ndash; The [[Cathedral of Our Lady of Peace]] in [[Honolulu, Hawaii]] is dedicated. Now the cathedral of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Honolulu]], it is the oldest [[Roman Catholic]] [[cathedral]] in continuous use in the [[United States]].
*  1843   &amp;ndash; [[Tivoli Gardens]],  one of the oldest still intact [[amusement park]]s in the world, opens in [[Copenhagen]], [[Denmark]].
*[[1863]] &amp;ndash; The [[Anglo-Satsuma War]] begins between the [[Satsuma Domain]] of [[Japan]] and the [[United Kingdom]] (Traditional [[Japanese calendar|Japanese date]]: July 2, 1863).
*[[1869]] &amp;ndash; The [[Meiji government]] in [[Japan]] establishes six new ministries, including one for [[Shinto]].
*[[1891]] &amp;ndash; [[San Sebastian Church]] in [[Manila]], the first all-steel church in [[Asia]], is officially inaugurated and blessed.
*[[1907]] &amp;ndash; Ordination in Constantinople of Fr. [[Raphael Morgan]], first African-American [[Orthodox Church|Orthodox]] priest, &quot;Priest-Apostolic&quot; to America and the West Indies.
*[[1909]] &amp;ndash; A group of mid-level [[Greek Army]] officers launches the [[Goudi coup]], seeking wide-ranging reforms.
*[[1914]] &amp;ndash; A male servant of [[United States|American]] [[architect]] [[Frank Lloyd Wright]] sets fire to the living quarters of the architect's [[Wisconsin]] home, [[Taliesin (studio)|Taliesin]], murders seven people and burns the living quarters to the ground.
*  1914   &amp;ndash; The [[Panama Canal]] opens to traffic with the transit of the cargo ship [[SS Ancon|Ancon]].
*  1914   &amp;ndash;  The First Russian Army, led by [[Pavel Rennenkampf]], enters [[Eastern Prussia]].
*[[1920]] &amp;ndash; [[Polish-Soviet War]]: [[Battle of Warsaw (1920)|Battle of Warsaw]] &amp;ndash; [[Poland|Poles]] defeat the [[Red Army]].
*[[1935]] &amp;ndash;  [[Will Rogers]] and [[Wiley Post]] are killed after their aircraft develops engine problems during takeoff in [[Barrow, Alaska]].
*[[1939]] &amp;ndash; 13 [[Junkers Ju 87|Stukas]] dive into the ground during a disastrous air-practice at Neuhammer. No survivors.
*[[1940]] &amp;ndash; An [[Italy|Italian]] submarine torpedoes and sinks the [[Greek cruiser Elli (1912)|Greek cruiser ''Elli'']] at [[Tinos]] harbour during peacetime, marking the most serious Italian provocation prior to the outbreak of the [[Greco-Italian War]] in October.
*[[1941]] &amp;ndash; Corporal [[Josef Jakobs]] is executed by firing squad at the [[Tower of London]] at 7:12am, making him the last person to be executed at the Tower for [[treason]].
*[[1942]] &amp;ndash; [[World War II]]: [[Operation Pedestal]] &amp;ndash; The [[SS Ohio|SS ''Ohio'']] reaches the island of [[Malta]] barely afloat carrying vital fuel supplies for the island's defenses.
*[[1944]] &amp;ndash; [[World War II]]: [[Operation Dragoon]] &amp;ndash; Allied forces land in [[southern France]].
*[[1945]] &amp;ndash; World War II: [[Victory over Japan Day]] &amp;ndash; [[Japan]] surrenders.
*  1945   &amp;ndash; World War II: [[Korean Liberation Day]].
*[[1947]] &amp;ndash; [[India]] gains [[Independence of India|Independence]] from the [[British Empire|British]] [[Indian Empire]] and joins the [[Commonwealth of Nations]].
*  1947   &amp;ndash; Founder of [[Pakistan]], [[Jinnah|Muhammad Ali Jinnah]] is sworn in as first [[Governor General of Pakistan]] in [[Karachi]].
*[[1948]] &amp;ndash; The [[South Korea|Republic of Korea]] is established south of the [[38th parallel north]].
*[[1950]] &amp;ndash; [[Srikakulam district]] is formed in [[Andhra Pradesh]], [[India]].
*[[1952]] &amp;ndash; [[Devon|Devon, United Kingdom]] A flashflood drenches the town of Lynmouth, killing 34 people.
*[[1954]] &amp;ndash; [[Alfredo Stroessner]] begins his dictatorship in [[Paraguay]].
*[[1960]] &amp;ndash; [[Republic of the Congo]] ([[Brazzaville]]) becomes independent from [[France]].
*[[1961]] &amp;ndash; [[Conrad Schumann]] flees from [[East Germany]] while on duty guarding the construction of the [[Berlin Wall]].
*[[1962]] &amp;ndash; [[James Joseph Dresnok]] defects to the [[Democratic People's Republic of Korea]] after running across the [[Korean DMZ]]. Dresnok still resides in the capital, [[Pyongyang]].
*[[1963]] &amp;ndash; Execution of [[Henry John Burnett]], the last man to be hanged in Scotland.
*  1963   &amp;ndash; President [[Fulbert Youlou]] is overthrown in the [[Republic of Congo]], after a [[Trois Glorieuses (1963)|three-day uprising]] in the capital.
*  1965   &amp;ndash; [[The Beatles]] play to nearly [[The Beatles' 1965 U.S. tour|60,000 fans at Shea Stadium]] in [[New York City]], in an event later seen as marking the birth of [[arena rock|stadium rock]].
*[[1969]] &amp;ndash; The [[Woodstock Music and Art Festival]] opens.
*[[1971]] &amp;ndash; [[President]] [[Richard Nixon]] completes the break from the [[gold standard]] by ending convertibility of the [[United States dollar]] into gold by foreign investors.
*   1971  &amp;ndash; [[Bahrain]] gains [[Bahrain Independence Day|independence]] from the [[United Kingdom]].
*[[1973]] &amp;ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: The [[United States]] bombing of [[Cambodia]] ends.
*[[1974]] &amp;ndash; [[Yuk Young-soo]], [[First Lady]] of [[South Korea]], is killed during an apparent assassination attempt upon [[President]] of [[South Korea]], [[Park Chung-hee]].
*[[1975]] &amp;ndash; [[Bangladesh]]'s founder [[Sheikh Mujibur Rahman]] is killed along with most members of his family during a military coup.
*  1975   &amp;ndash; [[Miki Takeo]] makes the first official pilgrimage to [[Yasukuni Shrine]] by an incumbent [[Prime Minister of Japan|prime minister]] on the anniversary of the end of [[World War II]].
*[[1977]] &amp;ndash; [[The Big Ear]], a [[radio telescope]] operated by [[Ohio State University]] as part of the [[SETI]] project, receives a radio signal from deep space; the event is named the &quot;[[Wow! signal]]&quot; from the notation made by a volunteer on the project.
*[[1984]] &amp;ndash; The [[Kurdistan Workers Party|PKK]] in [[Turkey]] starts a campaign of armed attacks upon the Turkish military
*[[1995]] &amp;ndash; In [[South Carolina]], [[Shannon Faulkner]] becomes the first female [[cadet]] matriculated at [[The Citadel, The Military College of South Carolina|The Citadel]] (she drops out less than a week later).
*[[1998]] &amp;ndash; [[Omagh Bombing|Omagh bomb]] in [[Northern Ireland]], the worst [[terrorism|terrorist]] incident of [[The Troubles]]
*[[1999]] &amp;ndash; [[Beni Ounif massacre]] in [[Algeria]]; some 29 people are killed at a false roadblock near the Moroccan border, leading to temporary tensions with [[Morocco]].
*[[2007]] &amp;ndash; An [[2007 Peru Earthquake|8.0-magnitude earthquake]] off the [[Pacific coast]] devastates [[Ica region|Ica]] and various regions of [[Peru]] killing 514 and injuring 1,090.

